Chile Central Bank to Maintain Pace of Daily Dollar Buying

-- B y   R a n d a l l   W o o d s   a n d   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-07-08T20:48:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-08/chile-central-bank-to-maintain-pace-of-daily-dollar-buying-1-.html
Chile ’s central bank will keep buying
$50 million a day in the coming month as part of a $12 billion
program to raise reserves and limit the peso’s gain, it said in
a statement today on its website.  The central bank will sell $757 million in inflation bonds
and $292 million in peso bonds in the coming month, it said. The
government will sell $162 million in peso bonds and $355 million
in inflation bonds, the central bank said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
